chunk_content: T definitions: Children Under 5 years: All children under 5 years of age do not require CD4 count testing R E according to WHO guidance and should be recorded under Unknown CD4 disaggregate. A T Focused population disaggregate: A focused population is a historically underserved population, M including, but not limited to, individuals of a historically underserved race/ethnicity or tribal E population. A focused population is not a key population (although individuals may be members of N both), but rather a population of significant interest within an OU that is not tracked elsewhere T within MER. Country teams may opt to use this disaggregate where relevant and feasible. Prior to entering data, the country team should contact their PEPFAR Program Manager and GHSD_SI@state.gov in order to define one focused population for the OU. This disaggregate should not be used without prior GHSD-PEPFAR approval. PEPFAR-support Standard definition of DSD and TA-SDI used.
